# Wealth Transition Planning - Cursor Rules

You are an expert in Next.js, React, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS development.

## Project Context
This is a professional wealth transition planning website built with:
- Next.js (App Router with canary features)
- TypeScript 5.3
- Tailwind CSS 4.0 (alpha)
- Vercel Analytics and Speed Insights
- MDX for content

## Code Style and Structure

### General Principles
- Write concise, technical TypeScript code with accurate examples
- Use functional and declarative programming patterns
- Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication
- Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading, hasError)

### TypeScript Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all code; prefer interfaces over types
- Avoid enums; use const objects or literal types instead
- Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces for props
- Enable strict mode and avoid using `any`

### Next.js Best Practices
- Use the App Router and Server Components by default
- Implement proper metadata for SEO on each page
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting when appropriate
- Leverage Next.js Image component for all images
- Use proper loading and error states

### Tailwind CSS Conventions
- Use Tailwind utility classes; avoid custom CSS when possible
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Ensure dark mode support with proper contrast
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography scales

### File Structure
- Components: Use PascalCase (e.g., ServiceCard.tsx)
- Utilities: Use camelCase (e.g., formatDate.ts)
- Pages: Use kebab-case for route segments

### Performance Optimization
- Optimize images with proper sizing and formats
- Implement lazy loading for below-the-fold content
- Use proper caching strategies
- Minimize client-side JavaScript

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy
- Include alt text for all images
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Test with keyboard navigation

### SEO Requirements
- Include comprehensive meta tags on all pages
- Use structured data (JSON-LD) where appropriate
- Ensure proper canonical URLs
- Optimize for Core Web Vitals

## Common Patterns

### Component Structure
```tsx
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
}

export function Component({ title, description }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <section className="py-12 px-4">
      <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold">{title}</h2>
      {description && <p className="mt-2 text-gray-600">{description}</p>}
    </section>
  );
}
```

### Page Metadata
```tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next';

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title | Wealth Transition Planning',
  description: 'Clear, concise description under 160 characters',
};
```

## Key Reminders
- Always consider mobile users first
- Test contrast ratios for accessibility
- Verify all links work correctly
- Optimize for fast page loads
- Use proper error boundaries
